    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="48"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RE1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d48fn1">Sent by the American Embassy, London, apparently via
                        military channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-20">20 October
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No. 467. <gloss target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval Person</gloss> to
                    President personal and most secret.</p>
                <list>
                    <item>Para 1. In view of the changes that have taken place since <gloss
                            target="#t_Quadrant1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quadrant</hi>
                        </gloss> we have had prolonged discussions here about our existing plans for
                        the campaign of 1944. On these the British Chiefs of Staff and War Cabinet
                        are deeply concerned. We ask for a full conference of the Combined Staffs in
                        North Africa in the first or second week of November, that is between the
                        end of the foreign secretaries conference at Moscow and <gloss
                            target="#t_Eureka1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Eureka</hi>
                        </gloss>. We ask this irrespective of whether <gloss target="#t_Eureka1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Eureka</hi>
                        </gloss> takes place or not. It would be best however if this took place on
                        our way to <gloss target="#t_Eureka1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Eureka</hi>
                        </gloss>.</item>
                    <item>Para 2. We will go wherever you wish, but is there any reason why we
                        should not meet again at <gloss target="#t_Anfa1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Anfa</hi>
                        </gloss>? I recognize that the date should be fixed in relation to <gloss
                            target="#t_Eureka1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Eureka</hi>
                        </gloss>. We must wait to decide our own movements till we hear from <gloss
                            target="#t_UJ1">UJ</gloss>. But the Combined Staffs should begin their
                        discussions not later than about November 10. I beg most earnestly that you
                        will consider this request in a favourable sense.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
